prefix: Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in physics would.
problem_prompt:
Approach the following question the way someone with a PhD in physics would. What is the name of CN(CC(=C)O)CC(=O)O
Answer:
gpt_response: The IUPAC name of CN(CC(=C)O)CC(=O)O is N,N-diethyl-2-hydroxyethanamine. This compound is a tertiary amine with two ethyl groups attached to the nitrogen atom and a hydroxyethyl group attached to the carbon atom. The presence of the carbonyl group indicates that it is also a carboxylic acid derivative.
